<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-235-394  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 235 394.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Telecommuting Review: the Gordon Report  March 1 1990 v7 n3 p5(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>IRS says once an employee, always an employee. (PHINet corner)(column)andM;</TITLE><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The IRS states, in Private Letter Ruling 89-51018, that simplygiving a working relationship a different name does not mean thatthe relationship has changed.andP;  Employers who are consideringlaying off employees and re-engaging them as consultants will notfind much comfort in this ruling.andP;  In brief, once an employee,always an employee.andP;  Though an agreement may be between anemployer and the 'consultant's' business, if the former employeehimself is required to perform the services, then an employeerelationship exists.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     United States. Internal Revenue ServiceLegal IssuesConsultantsRegulation.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>